title="Alex Nelson">Alex Nelson</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>Let <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {F}]]></fr:tex> be a field. There is a unique ring morphism <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\phi \colon \mathbb {Z}\to \mathbb {F}]]></fr:tex> where <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\phi (1)=1]]></fr:tex>. We define the <html:dfn
xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">Characteristic</html:dfn> of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {F}]]></fr:tex> to be the smallest positive integer <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[n]]></fr:tex> such that <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[(n)=\ker (\phi )]]></fr:tex>, if such an <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[n>0]]></fr:tex> exists. Otherwise the characteristic of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {F}]]></fr:tex> is 0.</fr:p><fr:p>We write <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathop {\textrm {char}}\nolimits (\mathbb {F})]]></fr:tex> for the characteristic of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {F}]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
 
   
