title="Alex Nelson">Alex Nelson</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>Let <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\Bbbk  / \mathbb {F}]]></fr:tex> be a <fr:link
type="local"
href="nt-000F.xml"
addr="nt-000F"
title="Field extension">Field extension</fr:link>. The <html:dfn
xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">Degree</html:dfn> of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\Bbbk  / \mathbb {F}]]></fr:tex>, denoted <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[[\Bbbk  : \mathbb {F}]]]></fr:tex>, is equal to <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\dim _{\mathbb {F}}(\Bbbk )]]></fr:tex> the dimension of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\Bbbk ]]></fr:tex> <fr:link
type="local"
href="nt-000I.xml"
addr="nt-000I"
title="Field extension is a vector space">as a vector space</fr:link> over <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {F}]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p><fr:p>If <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[[\Bbbk  : \mathbb {F}]<\infty ]]></fr:tex>, then we say <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\Bbbk  / \mathbb {F}]]></fr:tex> is a <html:dfn
xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">Finite Extension</html:dfn>.</fr:p></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree><fr:tree
