href="dummit-2004-abstract.xml"
addr="dummit-2004-abstract"
title="Abstract Algebra">Abstract Algebra</fr:link> Theorem 13.1.4</fr:meta></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>Let <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {F}]]></fr:tex> be a field, let <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[p(x)\in \mathbb {F}[x]]]></fr:tex> be a nonconstant irreducible polynomial of degree <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\deg (p)=n]]></fr:tex>, and let <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\Bbbk =\mathbb {F}[x]/(p(x))]]></fr:tex>. Let <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\alpha \in \Bbbk ]]></fr:tex> be the image of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[x]]></fr:tex> under the quotient map
<fr:tex
display="block"><![CDATA[\pi \colon \mathbb {F}[x]\twoheadrightarrow \Bbbk ,]]></fr:tex>
then <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\{1,\alpha ,…,\alpha ^{n-1}\}]]></fr:tex> is a basis for <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\Bbbk ]]></fr:tex> as a vector space over <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {F}]]></fr:tex>. In particular, <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[[\Bbbk  : \mathbb {F}]=n]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
 
   
